Stone of Nomakk is a decent common relic, held back largely by the fact that just 1 potency doesn't affect the secondary effect of your slimes, which is where a lot of the value of slimes comes from. If your deck is already capable of making an odd number of potency, this gets better as it takes you back to an even number, but that's fairly rare. I suppose the question is, do you get enough value (as a common relic) just by increasing the damage of your slimes by 1? That should fairly consistently be 3 damage a turn, and you can increase that number by playing more cards with command. That's similar to the damage that you get from cracked core, and is reasonable when put next to mercury hourglass (which is AOE, but it can be better since it's uncommon).

The main issue here is that 1 potency isn't enough to help increase the secondary effect of your slime at all, which makes this feel underwhelming. On the other hand, 2 potency is almost definitely too strong for a common relic. Considering that 2 potency gives you roughly 6 damage per turn as well as enchancing the secondary effects, It might need to be a rare.
